article.headline: New Hampshire 45, Villanova 17
article.story:
DURHAM, N.H. (AP)-- Ricky Santos completed 28 of 33 pass attempts
for 371 yards and five touchdowns to push the University of New
Hampshire to a 45-17 victory against Villanova University on
Saturday.

New Hampshire (4-0, 2-0) scored on their first play when Santos
threw a backwards pass to Mike Boyle who flipped the ball back to
Santos. He passed to David Ball for a 66-yard touchdown pass.

The teams traded touchdowns in the second quarter as New
Hampshire scored on drives of 97 and 93 yards. A 34-yard pass play
from Frank Jankowski to J.J. Outlaw pulled Villanova (2-2, 1-1)
within 21-10 but Boyle's 22-yard touchdown run pushed the advantage
back to 28-10.

A 22-yard Jankowski to Outlaw strike made it 28-17 at 4:47 but
Santos connected with Ball on an 18-yard pass play to close the
first half at 35-17.

New Hampshire opened the third quarter with a 77-yard drive that
culminated in a 14-yard Santos to Keith LeVan pass play to make it
42-17. Connor McCormick made a 34-yard field goal attempt to close
the scoring at 3:50 of the third quarter.<
